By Boluwatife Ezekiel Olaleye

Liverpool star, Mohamed Salah has finally reacted to Philippe Coutinho’s move to Barcelona.

The Egyptian international dropped a message for the Brazil international who completed a big money move to the Camp Nou on Monday.

Recall that Coutinho yesterday told The Reds fans that Salah can help the club to challenge for silverware in the coming seasons.

ALSO SEE: Why Neymar mocked Philippe Coutinho after Barcelona move

Salah took to his Twitter account on Wednesday, saying, “I really enjoyed playing with you even if it was for such a short time. I wish you all the best in your new adventure.”

Coutinho, who ended his five-year stay at Anfield, scored 12 goals and eight assists in 20 games in all competitions for Liverpool this season.

			
